The `nginx-proxy` duplicate block that had two `resources.limits.cpus` keys is now gone, along with all other YAML corruption from previous edits. Let me validate it parses correctly:

<tool name="execute_command">{"command": "python3 -c \"import yaml; d=yaml.safe_load(open(r'd:\\Github\\Crux-Webmail\\docker-compose.prod.yml')); print(f'Services found: {list(d[\"services\"].keys())}'); print('✅ Valid YAML')\"", "creation_policy": {"action": "always"}}
</tool>

The error moved to line 102 — let me see what's there:

<tool name="execute_command">{"command": "Get-Content 'd:\\Github\\Crux-Webmail\\docker-compose.prod.yml' -TotalCount 130 | Select-Object -First 40", "creation_policy": {"action": "always"}}
</tool>

Linea 102 — el error está en la transición entre MAIL STACK y MONITORING. Veo que hay comentarios sueltos al margen 0 (`# -------------------------------------------------------------------`) que rompen la sección `services:`. Voy a arreglar esto y además ver las líneas cercanas:

<tool name="execute_command">{"command": "python3 -c "
import yaml
try:
    with open(r'd:\\Github\\Crux-Webmail\\docker-compose.prod.yml') as f:
        d = yaml.safe_load(f)
except Exception as e:
    print('ERROR:', e)"
", "creation_policy": {"action": "always"}}
</tool>
